{"content": "Medicare won\u2019t pay room and board for your care in a facility unless the\nhospice medical team decides you need short-term inpatient care to manage\npain and other symptoms. This care must be in a Medicare-approved facility,\fSECTION 2: Find out if Medicare covers your test, item, or service 27\nlike a hospice facility, hospital, or skilled nursing facility that contracts with the\nhospice.\nMedicare also covers inpatient respite care, which is care you get in a\nMedicare-approved facility so that your usual caregiver (family member or\nfriend) can rest. ", "content_type": "text", "score": null, "meta": {"_split_id": 142, "_split_overlap": [{"doc_id": "d3ec555b8abaa7ce58ca34bdb28bffdd", "range": [0, 171]}, {"doc_id": "12ae24e8bccecde6f3e4afb623e6f540", "range": [389, 552]}]}, "id_hash_keys": ["content"], "embedding": null, "id": "d30b71b2aa7fa5be5ebf27939e001752"}